	* ordered magma
		\ links-to internal iihqgewkfaxwuyio
* proof
	* need: forall x y c:
		* se x y => se (x <> s) (y <> s)
		* se x y => se (s <> x) (s <> y)
	* one of them is enough to prove, because <> is commutative
	* i will use the
		* isomorphism of the 2 representations of semilattices
			\ links-to internal yfrehcdkxqrbrkoy
	* thus we need
		* x <> y = y => (x <> s) <> (y <> s) = (y <> s)
	* proving chain of equations
		* (x <> s) <> (y <> s)
		* = 
			* by associative of <>
		* (x <> y) <> (s <> s)
		* =
			* by assumption
		* y <> (s <> s)
		* =
			* by idempotence of <> 
		* y <> s